ially, metric performance degradation upon reference expansion becomes a new signal for brittleness, triggering refinement via neural architecture search or prompt optimization. The two loops interact symbiotically: improved metrics better guide reference selection (e.g., identifying under-covered regions), while richer references expose latent flaws in metrics. This closed, adaptive system enables the emergence of evaluation standards that are not only more aligned with human judgment but also resilient to linguistic variation and domain shifts. IMEF-Gen has broad implications for benchmark design, model development, and trustworthy AI, particularly in high-stakes applications such as education, healthcare, and legal text generation where evaluation validity is paramount.",
